<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-10T08:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-10T08:30:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Brazil/3380b:
                            Airgram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-10T09:30:00-04:00">May 10, 1943—9:30
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–1416. Embassy at Buenos Aires advises that Argentina imported crude
                            rubber from Brazil in amount of 4 kilos in January, 12,405 in February
                            and 7,648 in March, or a total of 20,057 for the first quarter.
                            Department would like explanation of these shipments in violation of
                            rubber agreement between Brazil and United States.<note n="39" xml:id="d619fn39">For the Department’s position on this trade, see
                                telegram No. 3012, August 11, to the Ambassador in Brazil, <ref target="#pg_674">p. 674</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>